</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uhestialadrow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hestia la Drow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 88<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/22/02 3:09 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: POG SOLOABLE</span><hr size=1> Done this with 6 guys...<br>
<br>
I don't think us wizzi can solo there, but a shamy can... <p><CENTER><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=48473"><img src="http://hestialadrow.free.fr/logohestia2.jpg"></a></CENTER>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=taelenskychaser>Taelen Skychaser</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/24/02 10:49 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> POG Soloing</span><hr size=1> I tried to solo a white horse once.  I got it down to 20% and had to gate due to low life.  I tried again and could never get root/snare to stick.  There's only so much running around you can do, hehe.  I would try to root, resist, run, root, resist, run, root, stick, try to snare, resist, root breaks, etc.  First time I tried I got a snare to stick but I don't recall why my life was so low.  I think I may have done something stupid like start with 70-80m and then used a ton before I got a snare to stick.  My point is, I got a horse down to 20%, so I believe solo'ing is possible.  This was when I was level 60 and before I had sunstrike.<br>
<br>
Now level 61....  and it seems that resists have changed a bit, at least it seems I get less resists on snares now.  I used to get resists once in a great while while rounding up mobs for quadding, now I virtually never get resists on atol's.  I went back to try again once but the zone was cleared, hehe.<br>
<br>
If anyone tries, let me know how it goes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aabramms>aabramms</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/31/02 8:15 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: POG Soloing</span><hr size=1> Yeah I can see it now: <br>
<br>
Level 60 wizard tryes to kite in POG, runs after mutant cloven man nukes once or twice then finds himself surrounded by more cloven men yelling at the top of their lungs &quot;Tolchuck him in the Gulliver Dim!!&quot;  *thwap* <br>
<br>
 <p>&lt;CENTER&gt;&lt;IMG SRC=&quot;http://aabramms.freewebspace.com/trolly2.jpg&quot; ALIGN=bottom HEIGHT=280&gt;&lt;/CENTER&gt;<br>
&lt;CENTER&gt;&lt;a target=&quot;new&quot; href=&quot;http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227072&quot;&gt;My Profile&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/CENTER&gt; </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=taelenskychaser>Taelen Skychaser</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/8/02 12:59 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: POG Soloing</span><hr size=1> I was up in PoG with my guild about a week ago.  They were ressing and stuff and I was bored and decided to try and kill a horse.  I was successful, but it was a little scary.  I am level 61.  I think I had 3 bubs of life left or so.<br>
<br>
This is what I found scary.  They are pretty mr, although snare stuck first cast I think I was lucky.  They try to root you CONSTANTLY.  If you are going to try this you better have really good mr.  Make sure to wear BD gear.  It also took most of my mana, I think I had quite a few partial resists, but overall not terrible.  It's the root and other spells they try to cast on you that is scary.  If you get rooted you better hope you can channel a gate. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lunaltoadsnatcher>Lunal Toadsnatcher</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 913<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/7/03 2:01 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: POG Soloing</span><hr size=1> I think it is doable to solo in PoG.  As the previous poster mentioned, be ready to gate at a moments notice.  Binding along the south wall and pulling from the plains far away from your bind spot should help if you have to gate.  After hunting a bit there, I want to try and solo something.  Got to learn better how to avoid the summoners, though.  And I got rooted a fair amount in my group, so gotta avoid that. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sanenyavs>SanenyaVS</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/11/03 4:32 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: POG Soloing</span><hr size=1> I've solo'd in PoG a couple times, once at 57 and at 61.. It's not too hard if you know what you're doing, but its really not worth it. The only mobs that dont summon are the gale wolfs, black/white horses(non named). They have ~20k hp and moderate resists.<br>
<br>
~Sanenya<br>
62 Sorcerer<br>
Venril Sathir <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=orsmoxlorr>Orsmo Xlorr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 773<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/11/03 7:51 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: POG Soloing</span><hr size=1> don't the horses drop the robes?<br>
